<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: 16 Apr 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Office International des Epizooties (OIE) Information
Department [edited]
<information.dept@oie.int>

Foot and Mouth Disease (Virus Type O) in Russia
--------------------------------------------------
(Date of previous outbreak of foot and mouth disease in Russia
reported to the OIE: April 2001).
Translation of information received on 16 Apr 2004 from Dr Evgueny A.
Nepoklonov, Head of the Main Veterinary Department, Ministry of
Agriculture and Food, Moscow: Date of the report: 16 Apr 2004.
Date of initial detection of animal health incident: 15 Apr 2004.
Estimated date of primary infection: 12 Apr 2004.
Location of the outbreak: Amur region (Amurskaya oblast), Tambovka
district, Sadovoye village (in the eastern part of the country).
Description of affected population: dairy cows aged 12 months.
Total number of animals in the outbreak: 141.
Total number of cases: 50.
Diagnostic tests used: enzyme immunoassay.
Source of agent / origin of infection: investigations under way.
Control measures:
- quarantine;
- movement control inside the country;
- modified stamping out;
- vaccination;
- zoning.
OIE Animal Health Information Department
<information.dept@oie.int>
